cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a neural network architecture for point-based trajectory classification using GPS data. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as basis expansion and segment-based information, which could potentially fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses Maxout activations, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and cryptography (cs.CR).
